reviews.text: Good experience and amazing place. We are here in May and it was damn hot throughout the day but was clear view. Early morning 4am it was bright and was an amazing experience watching the sun come out from behind those lime stone hills. Whole experience was wonderful. If you are not ok with the local Vietnamese food,then please be prepared with food n drinking water before getting on a cruise ride. Only Vietnamese food in limited quantity is served on board and it is good idea to carry some. Empty stomach will not allow you to enjoy the beautiful surroundings...

One of the best places on earth. You should visit once in your life. amazing limestone island (approx. 1970) surrounding this beach. 
you could visit caves and climb some of those islands .
visit the place by cruise tour including Kayaking, Swimming, learning how to cook like a Chef+ Dancing Nights & last but not least, unlimited! Vietnamese food :)) i hope we could visit again.

Look. The place is naturally stunning - the limestone formations, the trees, the colour of the water under the sky, the caves - all gorgeous! However, for a world heritage area, the pollution really takes away from the natural beauty of the place. There's trash everywhere - both on land and floating in the water. It's just gross! Our guide (a local) even recommended not to bathe in the water at the designated swimming spots as it wasn't exactly 'healthy'. I guess mass tourism has contributed, but having been to other world heritage sites that also have mass tourism but are still managed well and kept clean, surely this beautiful place could be cleaned up and a more ecological model of tourism adopted to bring in even more tourists and boost the local economy even more.

It's mesmerizing the perspective from here, totally amazing and certainly different from all I have ever seen. It helps if is a sunny day but even in different weather I am sure it will be great.
I suggest taking a boat trip of 2 times so you can sleep in here. It's certainly well worth the money! We also gone to a pearl factory as well as the caves &amp; did yoga at the sunrise. We additionally did kayak just swimming at sunset. You will find no more words for describing it! Just go!

Ha Long Bay or Alongues Bay (where the Dragon enters the Ocean), with about 1,969 limestone islets rising from the waters, is the best-known bay in Vietnam. The islands have an endless number of beaches, caves and caves. According to legend, when a great dragon that lived in the mountains ran to the sea, its tail dug valleys that later were filled with water, leaving only pieces of earth to the surface, that is to say, the numerous islands that are sighted in the bay. Ha Long Bay was declared a UNESCO World Heritage Site in 1993.

reviews.text:
Gili Island, Indonesia
Gili Trawangan, Gili Meno, Gili Air...
পাশাপাশি ৩ টি ছোট দ্বীপ। এই তিনটি দ্বীপে আসা যাওয়ার পথে এমন সবুজ মনোরম এই ক্ষুদ্র দ্বীপটির দেখা পাবেন।
আমরা যখন ছোট বেলায় বিটিভি তে তন্ময় হয়ে The Adventure Of Sinbad দেখতাম, তখন প্রায় পর্বেই এমন দ্বীপের দেখা পেতাম। যেখানে সিনবাদ তার বিশ্বস্ত ডুবার, লংগার, ফিরোজ, মীবদের নিয়ে জাহাজ নোঙ্গর করতেন!
যেভাবে যাবেনঃ By Air Dhaka- Kualalumpur- Bali. তারপরBy Fast Boat Bali - Gili Island.
Beautiful island of water. The beach is stunning! The sunrise and sunset magical. Lotbof tourist think it is part of Bali, but it is not. It is part of Lombok.

Beautiful hidden paradise on the small island. Has a lot of cheap accommodations by great facilities. Easy to go around the island. Having a horse car; diving; snorkeling; having sunset trip; fishing trip etc. There are a lots of restaurants for lunch/dinner and breakfast as well. 

To come the island just need a taxi from Lombok Airport to Bangsal Harbor (the main harbor to Gili). Then, there are Slow Boat/Speed Boat/Fastboat that you could find there to the island. All of the transportations you may get in public or book for your own.

we book a villa in advanced....turn out they are still renovating, so the room was dusty. we have to pay 200k for 2horse ride for 5people+bagage.....and instantly regretted it. should just find a villa near the dock instead. the island is very quiet and secluded. we dont really enjoy our time here
The most beautiful island in Indonesia. Relax, calm, great views, good restaurants, amazing beaches and sea. Great place to dive or snorkel.
